snippet.textDisplay: I am loving this new coke bharat. Vastness of bharatiya music and songs with a hint of fusion taste to it. It gets bharat a step more closer to each other on a meaningful level and it introduces the world to the frankly insane diversity in every aspect bharat possess especially in songs, folk songs, and music.

snippet.textDisplay: Though my roots lie in the mountains of Uttarakhand, destiny carried me elsewhere. My father, serving in the Assam Rifles, brought my mother and me along when I was barely a year old, and so the North East became the cradle of my childhood. Even after twenty-six years, the names of Jorhat, Nagnimara, Okhrul, Dimapur, and Imphal return to me like gentle whispers from the past — places that still breathe within me, tender and unforgettable. ❤
